 <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm"><strong>What is a semi-solid-state power bank and should I OEM one?</strong> Semi-solid-state power banks use a gel electrolyte instead of liquid, eliminating thermal runaway risk while delivering 25-35% higher energy density and 500-800+ cycle life. At just a <strong>15-25% price premium</strong> over Li-polymer, they are becoming the new standard for premium power banks in 2026, especially for brands targeting the EU and China markets where new safety regulations take effect this year. WOWOHCOOL offers <a href="/products/power-bank/semi-solid-state/" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">semi-solid-state power bank OEM from 5,000mAh to 27,000mAh</a> with PD 3.1 up to 140W.</p>
