 <section id="what-is" class="mb-16">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">1. What Is a Semi-Solid-State Battery?</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">A semi-solid-state battery replaces the liquid electrolyte found in conventional Li-polymer cells with a gel-like or paste electrolyte. This isn't a full solid-state battery, which uses a solid ceramic electrolyte and isn't yet mass-produced for consumer electronics. It's a hybrid, the best of both worlds.</p>
 <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
 <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
 <thead><tr class="bg-brandBlue text-white text-[11px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest"><th class="p-3 text-left">Feature</th><th class="p-3 text-left">Conventional Li-Polymer</th><th class="p-3 text-left">Semi-Solid-State</th></tr></thead>
 <tbody class="text-slate-600">
 <tr class="border-b border-slate-100"><td class="p-3 font-bold">Electrolyte</td><td class="p-3">Liquid</td><td class="p-3">Gel/paste</td></tr>
 <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold">Energy Density</td><td class="p-3">Baseline</td><td class="p-3">+25-35% higher</td></tr>
 <tr class="border-b border-slate-100"><td class="p-3 font-bold">Thermal Runaway Risk</td><td class="p-3">Present</td><td class="p-3">Near-zero</td></tr>
 <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold">Cycle Life</td><td class="p-3">300-500 cycles</td><td class="p-3">500-800+ cycles</td></tr>
 <tr class="border-b border-slate-100"><td class="p-3 font-bold">Production Maturity</td><td class="p-3">Mass market</td><td class="p-3">Scaling rapidly</td></tr>
 <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold">Price Premium</td><td class="p-3">Baseline</td><td class="p-3">+15-25%</td></tr>
 </tbody>
 </table>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">The key advantage for your brand: <strong>semi-solid-state cells don't catch fire.</strong> Even when punctured, overcharged, or exposed to high temperatures, the gel electrolyte doesn't ignite. For a brand selling power banks through Amazon FBA or retail distribution, that's a product liability game-changer.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">According to <a href="https://about.bnef.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange underline">BloombergNEF</a>, semi-solid-state batteries offer 30% higher energy density than conventional Li-polymer cells while eliminating thermal runaway risk. This combination of safety and performance has made semi-solid-state the fastest-growing segment in the power bank industry, with major brands transitioning their product lines to use this technology advantage.</p>
 </div>
 </section>

