 <section id="why-oem" class="mb-16">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">2. Why Semi-Solid-State Matters for OEM/ODM Brands</h2>
 <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-5 rounded-r-xl mb-6">
 <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm italic">"Last year, Marcus, a procurement manager for a European electronics distributor, received a shipment of 5,000 standard Li-polymer power banks. Three units swelled during the 4-hour aging test. Two more failed QC after the drop test. He rejected the entire batch and lost six weeks. His CEO wanted to know why they weren't using safer cells."</p>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">This scenario plays out more often than most buyers admit. Here's why gel electrolyte technology solves it:</p>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-brandBlue mb-2 mt-6">Thermal Safety Is Non-Negotiable</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The liquid electrolyte in conventional Li-polymer batteries is flammable. These batteries eliminate the liquid electrolyte entirely, removing the fire risk at the chemical level. For brands selling in the EU or shipping via air freight, this safety advantage is increasingly important.</p>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">Higher Density Means Slimmer Products</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">A semi-solid-state cell delivers roughly 30% higher energy density. That translates to a slimmer power bank with the same capacity, or higher capacity in the same form factor. WOWOHCOOL's WOP09 series achieves 10,000mAh in a profile 50% thinner than standard.</p>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">Longer Cycle Life, Better Brand Reputation</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">500-800 cycles vs. 300-500 means fewer returns and better reviews. <a href="/products/power-bank/" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">Browse our semi-solid-state power bank lineup &rarr;</a></p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">"The shift to semi-solid-state is the most significant battery safety advancement I've seen in my career," says Nina Nico, OEM Technical Lead at WOWOHCOOL. "Brands that adopt this technology now are not just reducing product liability, they are building a powerful safety narrative that resonates with today's quality-conscious consumers and retail buyers."</p>

 <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-5 mt-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-green-800 text-sm mb-2">Brands Already Shipping Semi-Solid-State (June 2026)</h3>
 <ul class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
 <li><strong>BMX "SolidSafe"</strong> — 6.8mm ultra-thin, Qi2 magnetic, from $59 (<a href="https://www.androidauthority.com/bmx-semi-solid-state-battery-power-banks-3674759/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange underline">Android Authority</a>)</li>
 <li><strong>TORRAS</strong> — EV battery tech positioning, thermal management focus ($80-120)</li>
 <li><strong>Statik "State"</strong> — 5K power bank, praised in <a href="https://www.macworld.com/article/2959404/statik-state-power-bank-5k-review.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange underline">Macworld review</a></li>
 <li><strong>Momax</strong> — Qi2 25W magnetic with semi-solid cells, EU market</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-2">The technology has hit consumer retail — now is the time for OEM brands to secure supply chain positioning before demand outpaces production capacity.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <section id="evaluate-supplier" class="mb-16">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">3. How to Evaluate a Semi-Solid-State Supplier</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Finding a legitimate manufacturer is harder than it sounds. Several factories claim semi-solid-state capability but are actually shipping enhanced Li-polymer with a marketing label.</p>
 <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
 <div><h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue text-sm mb-1">1. Request Cell-Level Test Reports</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Ask for cycle life test data at 1C charge/discharge rate (should exceed 500 cycles), thermal runaway test results, energy density measurements, and UN38.3 certification.</p></div>
 <div><h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue text-sm mb-1">2. Ask About Electrolyte Formulation</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">A legitimate manufacturer should describe their gel polymer electrolyte without hesitation. Look for "in-situ polymerization" or patent filings.</p></div>
 <div><h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue text-sm mb-1">3. Visit or Video Tour the Factory</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">"When Chen-Wei visited his supplier's factory in Shenzhen, he asked to see the electrolyte mixing line. The factory manager showed him a dry room with specialized equipment, not the standard liquid filling line. That's when he knew the technology was real."</p></div>
 <div><h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue text-sm mb-1">4. Verify Certifications</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Semi-solid-state cells require UN38.3 certification for air shipping. Request the certificate and verify it covers your specific cell model.</p></div>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Red flags: can't explain cell technology technically, refuses video tour, uncertified test labs, pricing too close to standard Li-polymer.</p>

 <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange rounded-r-xl p-5 mt-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue text-sm mb-2">Certification Checklist for Importers</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Before placing your OEM order, verify that your supplier provides these certifications for semi-solid-state power banks:</p>
 <ul class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
 <li><strong>UN38.3</strong>, required for air transport, verifies cell-level safety under simulated flight conditions</li>
 <li><strong>CE / RoHS</strong>, mandatory for EU market entry, confirms electromagnetic compatibility and restricted substance compliance</li>
 <li><strong>FCC</strong>, required for US market, certifies radio frequency emissions are within legal limits</li>
 <li><strong>MSDS</strong>, Material Safety Data Sheet for lithium battery shipping documentation</li>
 <li><strong>Nail penetration test report</strong>, verifies thermal runaway safety claim for semi-solid-state cells</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-2">WOWOHCOOL provides all documentation with every OEM order and assists with regional certification requirements for 50+ countries.</p>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-xl p-5 mt-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-red-700 text-sm mb-2">Case Study: Why Verification Matters — Donut Lab Fraud (June 2026)</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">In June 2026, Finnish startup <a href="https://electrek.co/2026/06/08/donut-lab-solid-state-battery-exposed-lithium-ion-fraud/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange underline">Donut Lab was exposed</a> for marketing standard lithium-ion cells as "solid-state batteries." The company raised $25M from 1,300+ investors and reached a $1.25B valuation before independent testing by 20+ battery experts proved the cells were ordinary NCM chemistry — not the claimed 400 Wh/kg sodium-ion solid-state. This case underlines why OEM buyers must independently verify cell-level test reports and never rely solely on marketing claims.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <section id="pd31" class="mb-16">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
