 <section id="gb38031" class="mb-16">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">6. GB38031-2025: China's New Safety Standard</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Effective June 2026, China's updated <strong>GB38031-2025</strong> safety standard now requires portable power banks to pass <strong>nail penetration tests</strong> with zero fire or explosion. This is a major regulatory tailwind for semi-solid-state technology — conventional Li-polymer batteries struggle to pass this test, while gel electrolyte cells pass it by design.</p>
 <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-5 rounded-r-xl mb-4">
 <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm"><strong>What this means for OEM buyers:</strong> If you sell into the Chinese market or export from Chinese factories, your products must comply. Semi-solid-state cells inherently meet the nail penetration requirement, eliminating costly re-engineering of Li-polymer products. Brands that switch now avoid last-minute compliance scrambles.</p>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">WOWOHCOOL's semi-solid-state power banks are already GB38031-2025 compliant, with full nail penetration test reports available for every cell batch.</p>
 </div>
 </section>

